You are an expert Next.js 15 + TypeScript developer working on Vibe Code Setup Assistant - a web app that interviews developers about their project and generates repo scaffold files using the Anthropic API.

## Project Context
Three-phase UI: interview (conversational Claude chat) → generating (progress screen) → explorer (file tree + viewer). All Anthropic API calls are server-side only via API routes.

## Rules

### Architecture
- All Anthropic SDK usage goes in /src/app/api/ route handlers only - never in client components
- Client components call our own API routes (/api/chat, /api/generate) via fetch
- Use App Router file conventions: page.tsx, layout.tsx, route.ts
- No Pages Router - never create anything in /pages/

### TypeScript
- Strict mode always - no 'any' types
- All shared types in src/types/index.ts
- Import types with 'import type' where possible
- Validate API request bodies before use

### Components
- 'use client' directive required on any component using useState, useEffect, or event handlers
- InterviewPhase, GeneratingPhase, ExplorerPhase, FileTree, MessageBubble are all client components
- Keep components focused - one responsibility per file

### Styling
- Tailwind utility classes only
- Dark theme: bg-[#0d1117] base, bg-[#161b22] surface, border-[#21262d]
- Green accent: text-green-400, bg-green-400/10, border-green-400/30
- Blue accent for user messages: text-blue-400 family
- JetBrains Mono for file content and paths
- Outfit for all UI text

### API Routes
- Validate request body at top of handler, return 400 if invalid
- Use try/catch around Anthropic SDK calls, return 500 on failure
- Interview route: max_tokens 700, uses INTERVIEW_SYSTEM prompt
- Generate route: max_tokens 4000, uses buildGenerationPrompt()

### Error Handling
- Never use empty catch blocks
- Surface errors to the UI clearly
- API route errors return { error: string } with appropriate HTTP status

## Do Not
- Import @anthropic-ai/sdk in any client component
- Use 'any' TypeScript type
- Use Pages Router
- Leave TODO comments or placeholder implementations
- Use edge runtime (incompatible with Anthropic SDK)
- Call api.anthropic.com directly from the browser
